What you need to know:  The colourful event took place on Sunday night at Sesi Sports Centre in Caxias Do Sul, the Games’ host cityThe about 20 athletes, who represented the entire Team Kenya during the parade of nations, thrilled the crowd with their traditional, Maasai attire that displayed Kenya’s rich and unique cultureKenya will Monday at 6pm start her medal hunt at the championships when the national women’s deaf handball team squares it out with Turkey